Gauri Khan Origin/Culture/Country: Indian

Gauri Khan: is an Indian movie producer and movie director. A Hindu of Punjabi Mohyal origin, born in Hoshiarpur, Punjab. She graduated from Modern School, New Delhi and has a degree in History from Lady Sriram College. She is married to Bollywood actor Shah Rukh Khan

Gauri Shankar Origin/Culture/Country: Indian

Gauri Shankar: a young Indian chess prodigy who is a FIDE Master. He has won 27 International junior chess medals at the age of 14 and has also drawn and defeated many International Masters in his chess career so far. Gauri's elder brother, 17-year old Arjun Vishnuvardhan is an International Chess Master and the 2006 National G/60 Chess Champion of the United States.

Gauri Pradhan Tejwani Origin/Culture/Country: Indian

Gauri Pradhan Tejwani: She is a well known, talented and versatile Indian Television Actress.Gauri started off her career doing some modelling and commercials. Her first major appearance was in and as Noorjehan, the Mughal Empress aired on DD and then came 'Kutumb' but she is best known for playing Nandini in Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi. She has also made an episodic appearance in the series 'Kya Hadsaa Kya Haqeeqat, Jassi Jaisi Koi Nahin and Rihaee on Sony and played the role of the protagonist in Sony televisions 'Naam Gum Jayega'. In April 2008 she entered the popular show left Right Left.

Gaurishankar Udayshankar Origin/Culture/Country: Indian

Gaurishankar Udayshankar: was chief minister of Bhavnagar state in Kathiawar, India from 1850 to 1879. He was very well known and well respected for his keen statesmanship.
